claws into him at the prom?

05:15.440 --> 05:17.274
Yeah. He was warm for your form.

05:17.359 --> 05:19.902
Well, he seemed like
a sweet little shrimp.

05:21.571 --> 05:24.073
But then he turned into an octopus.

05:24.324 --> 05:25.533
Artie! Artie, no! Stop!

05:25.617 --> 05:29.078
Marge. Marge, you know you
can't resist my busy hands.

05:29.496 --> 05:31.288
Artie, get off of me!

05:32.958 --> 05:35.126
Well, I think you should
get in touch with him,

05:35.210 --> 05:38.546
you know, just to congratulate
him on his success.

05:40.132 --> 05:43.843
Well, I suppose I could
write him a letter.

05:43.927 --> 05:46.637
Are you nuts? E
- mail, female.

05:48.015 --> 05:49.932
You just tell us what you want to say.

05:51.560 --> 05:54.520
Okay, hold onto your hats.

05:55.814 --> 05:57.023
Dear Artie.

05:57.107 --> 05:58.816
Dear Hottie.

05:59.026 --> 06:02.611
Congratulations on your
recent TV appearance.

06:02.779 --> 06:06.449
I want to sex you up.
Your love slave, Marge.

06:06.783 --> 06:10.161
You can't use the word
"sex" on the Internet.

06:10.370 --> 06:11.620
Watch me!

06:26.178 --> 06:28.804
Anti-trust suit.
Anti-trust suit...

06:30.640 --> 06:32.641
A note from Marge Simpson?

06:32.893 --> 06:35.311
Well, isn't that a coincidence?

06:35.395 --> 06:36.937
I was just thinking about her.

06:37.647 --> 06:40.066
For the last 20 years.

06:49.785 --> 06:51.786
Mom, did you sleep
well at your sisters'?

06:51.870 --> 06:53.245
Mmm-hmm.

06:54.998 --> 06:56.791
Whoo! Mmm.

06:56.917 --> 06:58.042
For you.

06:58.126 --> 06:59.126
Ooh!

06:59.211 --> 07:02.296
Here's to a happy, well-rested Marge.

07:05.133 --> 07:08.302
Hey, a helicopter's landing on our lawn.

07:08.386 --> 07:09.678
Let's approach with caution.

07:15.185 --> 07:18.771
Unguarded breakfasts.
The sweetest taboo.

07:20.982 --> 07:22.691
Ooh.

07:25.403 --> 07:28.114
Well, well, Marge Bouvier.

07:28.198 --> 07:29.406
Artie Ziff?

07:29.991 --> 07:31.200
Oh.

07:31.284 --> 07:33.869
That e-mail. Look, I got a
little drunk and we were...

07:33.954 --> 07:36.288
I'm not surprised you
want me back in your life.

07:36.373 --> 07:38.791
You can't spell party without Artie,

07:38.875 --> 07:41.377
if you misspell party. Or Artie.

07:42.254 --> 07:43.254
How you doing?

07:43.338 --> 07:44.672
Look, it's great to see you,

07:44.756 --> 07:47.383
but you should know I'm happily married.

07:47.467 --> 07:49.385
Married? Was it consummated?

07:49.469 --> 07:50.845
Pretty much, yeah.

07:53.390 --> 07:54.598
What's going on?

07:54.683 --> 07:56.642
Homer, don't talk with your mouth full.

07:56.726 --> 07:58.811
I've told you before, it's rude!

07:58.895 --> 08:01.897
Oh-ho. Trouble in paradise.

08:02.858 --> 08:06.318
Hey, Marge! It's that guy
who couldn't get any off you!

08:06.736 --> 08:09.280
How would you all like
to take a ride with me?

08:09.364 --> 08:10.573
You're the old flame.

08:14.411 --> 08:17.663
Homer, Marge, I have a
rather delicate proposition.

08:17.956 --> 08:19.039
Spill it, moneybags.

08:20.292 --> 08:22.585
Yes, I do have everything,

08:23.086 --> 08:25.921
but yet I often wonder what life
with Marge would've been like.

08:26.006 --> 08:28.507
It's like being married
to my best friend,

08:28.592 --> 08:30.301
and he lets me feel his boobs.

08:31.636 --> 08:32.803
Homie!

08:33.429 --> 08:35.472
Homer, I will give you $1, 000,000

08:35.557 --> 08:37.433
to let me spend a weekend alone

08:37.808 --> 08:39.058
with your wife.

08:40.437 --> 08:43.022
Mmm. A million dollars. Wait a minute.

08:43.231 --> 08:46.692
How much sex would be involved?
Because if it's some...

08:46.943 --> 08:50.362
No, no, no. All I want is to show her

08:50.447 --> 08:53.073
what life would be
like had she chosen me.

08:53.408 --> 08:55.242
Artie, that's a sick idea.

08:55.327 --> 08:56.952
Come on, Homer. We're leaving.

09:02.417 --> 09:04.043
Just think about it!

09:04.127 --> 09:05.669
You'll win her yet, Artie.

09:06.004 --> 09:08.797
I mean, Arr-tie!

09:11.968 --> 09:13.969
Hey, where's our parents?

09:18.308 --> 09:20.226
Hey, Marge, I just thought of something.

09:20.310 --> 09:21.435
What?

09:21.645 --> 09:24.813
If we had Artie's money, I
could get that snoring surgery.

09:24.898 --> 09:28.734
Plus at least two of those other
surgeries I desperately need.

09:29.653 --> 09:33.447
No way, no how. I'll
get used to the snoring.

09:33.615 --> 09:37.159
Just like I got used to saying
"Courteney Cox-Arquette. "

09:37.327 --> 09:41.622
Besides, I like some of
the noises you make in bed.

09:44.584 --> 09:48.003
One squeaking spring symphony coming up.

09:53.510 --> 09:57.513
Wow! Homer, that was amazing!

09:57.597 --> 09:58.931
Yeah, I...

10:09.359 --> 10:11.527
Honey, did you get any sleep?

10:13.238 --> 10:14.989
Oh, I'm so sorry.

10:17.867 --> 10:20.369
Are you snoring while you're awake?

10:20.745 --> 10:22.371
Huh?

10:24.749 --> 10:28.544
You need that surgery.
We'll have to call Artie.

10:29.629 --> 10:33.882
Okay, Ziff. You get her for
the weekend, but no funny stuff.

10:34.342 --> 10:37.177
And by funny stuff,
I mean hand-holding,

10:37.262 --> 10:39.638
goo-goo eyes, misdirected woo,

10:39.723 --> 10:41.974
which is pretty much any John Woo film.

10:42.058 --> 10:43.642
Your wife's virtues shall remain

10:43.727 --> 10:46.478
as untouched as Bill Gates' weight room.

10:49.149 --> 10:53.360
Remember, Homie, I'm doing
this for us. See you on Monday,

11:09.210 --> 11:13.088
This round's on me, Moe!
I got a big payday coming.

11:13.423 --> 11:16.425
Yeah. Homer sold his
wife for a million bucks.

11:16.676 --> 11:21.263
I didn't sell her. I just
rented her to an old boyfriend.

11:21.639 --> 11:23.140
Gee, a million bucks.

11:23.224 --> 11:27.561
That's gonna buy him a lot of
swings in the old batting cage.

11:28.897 --> 11:30.606
Looks like everyone's a winner.

11:30.690 --> 11:32.608
