an excuse to get in my mouth.

14:22.195 --> 14:24.530
Keep your money. I'm going home.

14:30.828 --> 14:34.039
Stop looking at me! Keep dancing!

14:34.123 --> 14:35.582
Don't you know how to dance?

14:35.917 --> 14:37.167
Watch me!

14:47.345 --> 14:50.013
Aw! He's gonna sleep tonight.

14:51.933 --> 14:56.812
Oh, guys, it was horrible. I saw
Marge kissing a far superior man.

14:56.896 --> 14:58.772
Well, if it makes you feel any better,

14:58.856 --> 15:00.315
he's probably doing her right now.

15:02.151 --> 15:04.653
Oh, yeah. Make me the bad guy.

15:04.737 --> 15:06.572
My life here is over.

15:07.657 --> 15:11.785
Lenny, how'd you like to leave
town with me and never come back?

15:11.869 --> 15:13.412
Sounds like a plan.

15:13.496 --> 15:14.580
Then it's settled.

15:14.914 --> 15:17.124
We leave Springfield forever.

15:18.543 --> 15:20.085
What'd I miss? Anything good?

15:25.800 --> 15:27.634
That's $912.

15:27.802 --> 15:29.970
Send the bill to
Baron Von Kiss-a-lot.

15:30.054 --> 15:31.179
No problemo.

15:34.559 --> 15:36.810
This just arrived, Herr Baron.

15:37.353 --> 15:39.354
Okay, who's the wise guy?

15:40.857 --> 15:45.027
Oh, Homie, I'm so glad to
see... A tape on the bed?

15:51.200 --> 15:52.993
Marge, if you're watching this

15:53.077 --> 15:54.202
then it means I've figured out

15:54.287 --> 15:59.625
how to work the camera. Last night
I crashed a certain fake prom.

16:00.043 --> 16:02.836
That's right. Artie Ziff's fake prom.

16:04.047 --> 16:05.464
Homer was there?

16:05.548 --> 16:08.216
I saw something terrible
and I can't even say it.

16:08.301 --> 16:11.136
So I'll have these
two dolls do it for me.

16:11.387 --> 16:13.430
Kiss me, Artie.

16:13.514 --> 16:14.931
With pleasure.

16:15.224 --> 16:17.059
Homer's a big jerk.

16:18.895 --> 16:20.646
Ooh.

16:20.730 --> 16:22.439
But I can explain!

16:22.523 --> 16:23.857
I'm leaving you, Marge.

16:23.983 --> 16:27.110
The next time you see my name
will be in the hobo obituaries.

16:27.195 --> 16:30.739
Don't worry about the kids. I'll
drop them off with Patty and Selma.

16:30.823 --> 16:33.241
Patty and Selma? Screw that!

16:33.326 --> 16:34.910
Just run the camera, you little...

16:38.247 --> 16:40.040
Goodbye, my darling.

16:57.850 --> 16:58.850
Oh.

16:58.935 --> 17:02.145
It's no good. Everything
reminds me of Marge.

17:08.694 --> 17:10.028
I know what you're going through.

17:10.113 --> 17:12.280
We're coming up on Mount Carlmore.

17:14.701 --> 17:17.202
I carved that one wonderful summer.

17:17.286 --> 17:18.453
What did Carl think?

17:18.954 --> 17:20.914
You know, we've never discussed it.

17:37.515 --> 17:40.475
Do you have any jobs for
a man who wants to die?

17:40.560 --> 17:41.601
Something indoorsy.

17:41.686 --> 17:43.353
Close to a bathroom?

17:43.646 --> 17:47.607
I'll put you on rig 13 as soon
as they burn off the corpses.

17:48.985 --> 17:50.819
This job will be perfect.

17:50.903 --> 17:53.113
I'm gonna leave this
world the way I entered it,

17:53.197 --> 17:56.533
dirty, screaming, and torn
away from the woman I love.

17:56.617 --> 17:59.870
Oh. Quick and pointless.
That's the death for me.

18:00.163 --> 18:02.497
Thank you. You've been very helpful.

18:02.623 --> 18:04.916
Dad just got a library
card in West Springfield.

18:05.001 --> 18:06.626
He checked out 10 books on oil rigging

18:06.711 --> 18:08.170
and a book called Dying for Dummies.

18:08.254 --> 18:09.921
He must have taken a job

18:10.006 --> 18:11.923
in the West Springfield oil patch.

18:12.008 --> 18:13.383
That's practically a death sentence!

18:14.552 --> 18:17.763
What happened now?
Homer bowled a 300 game?

18:17.930 --> 18:20.807
Grampa, that happened
a year and a half ago.

18:20.892 --> 18:22.976
We have to go save Homer.

18:23.311 --> 18:26.021
But West Springfield's three
times the size of Texas.

18:26.105 --> 18:28.190
We'll never find him there.

18:29.192 --> 18:30.692
Unless...

18:34.030 --> 18:36.948
I really appreciate you
helping me find Homer.

18:37.033 --> 18:38.366
Think nothing of it, Marge.

18:38.451 --> 18:40.076
I hope we can always be friends.

18:40.161 --> 18:41.161
Of course.

18:41.245 --> 18:42.370
With privileges?

18:42.538 --> 18:44.331
Mmm? Mmm?

18:45.500 --> 18:47.083
Does that work on anyone?

18:47.460 --> 18:48.502
No.

18:48.878 --> 18:51.004
But when it does, hello!

19:00.056 --> 19:02.474
Another oil well successfully capped.

19:02.558 --> 19:04.601
Let's raise our goggles in triumph.

19:22.745 --> 19:26.081
Oh, no! This is how
Faceless Joe lost his legs!

19:32.922 --> 19:36.132
Looks like we're goners.
Oh, well. Circle of life.

19:39.554 --> 19:40.720
Marge!

19:43.766 --> 19:45.016
Climb up!

19:47.562 --> 19:49.521
Ain't you coming, Homer? Why?

19:49.605 --> 19:51.690
So I can watch my wife
spend the rest of her life

19:51.774 --> 19:53.567
in the arms of another man?

19:53.651 --> 19:55.944
I don't think so. Good day!

19:56.112 --> 19:57.279
But Homer...

19:57.363 --> 19:58.947
We said good day!

20:05.830 --> 20:08.039
Listen to me, Homer! You've won!

20:08.124 --> 20:11.960
You own Marge's heart, and that's
something I could never buy.

20:12.420 --> 20:13.670
Woo-hoo!

20:15.214 --> 20:17.173
There's nothing on
that helicopter for me.

20:17.258 --> 20:18.717
Don't be so sure.

20:20.094 --> 20:21.887
Carl Carlson?

20:28.895 --> 20:31.479
Artie, thanks for saving my life.

20:32.273 --> 20:34.608
Now, I believe there's the little
matter of the million dollars.

20:34.692 --> 20:36.526
We can't take his money.

20:36.611 --> 20:39.321
Oh. I can't take his money.

20:39.655 --> 20:43.158
I can't print my own money.
I have to work for money.

20:43.326 --> 20:45.785
Why don't I just lie down and die?

20:45.912 --> 20:47.412
Now, Homer, if there's one thing

20:47.496 --> 20:49.414
you should've learned from all this,

20:49.498 --> 20:53.043
it's that I'm rich, rich, rich! And now,

20:55.004 --> 20:57.714
I bid you adieu!

21:00.343 --> 21:02.677
I'm Artie Ziff!

21:04.972 --> 21:07.140
I gotta hand it to Artie Ziff, Marge.

21:07.224 --> 21:09.517
That little nerd saved my life.

21:09.852 --> 21:11.227
And our marriage.

21:11.312 --> 21:14.397
With his latest invention,
the snore converter.

21:16.317 --> 21:17.943
Goodnight, Homie.

21:19.028 --> 21:20.654
Goodnight, honey.

21:31.749 --> 21:34.292
He's a loser, Marge. Dump him!

21:34.377 --> 21:37.712
I travel the world and the seven seas

21:38.214 --> 21:41.508
